{"id":1038,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":1038,"title":"Reuben","subtitle":"","short_title":"Reuben","uri":"/scriptures/bd/reuben","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/reuben.t1","order":".000.3432"},[".title","Reuben"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/reuben.p1","order":".000.3433"},"Eldest son of Jacob (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/29.32"},"Gen. 29:32"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/30.14"},"30:14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/35.22-23"},"35:22–23"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/37.21-22,29"},"37:21–22, 29"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/42.22,37"},"42:22, 37"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/26.5"},"Num. 26:5"],"); settled east of Jordan (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/32"},"Num. 32"],"); the special characteristics of the tribe are referred to in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/49.3"},"Gen. 49:3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/33.6"},"Deut. 33:6"],". The tribe’s numbers gradually diminished, and though it continued to exist as a tribe, it became politically unimportant. In",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/5.15-16"},"Judg. 5:15–16"],", it is reproached by Deborah for its indifference during a time of national peril. For other references see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/4.12"},"Josh. 4:12"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/13.15-23"},"13:15–23"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/18.7"},"18:7"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/22"},"22"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/5.1,3,18"},"1 Chr. 5:1, 3, 18"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezek/48.6-7,31"},"Ezek. 48:6–7, 31"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/7.5"},"Rev. 7:5"],". Levite cities in,",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/20.8"},"Josh. 20:8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/21.7,36"},"21:7, 36"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/6.63,78"},"1 Chr. 6:63, 78"],". Dathan and Abiram, men of Reuben,",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/16.1"},"Num. 16:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/11.6"},"Deut. 11:6"],"; Bohan, son of Reuben,",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/15.6"},"Josh. 15:6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/18.17"},"18:17"],"."],["div",{"id":"p2","uri":"/scriptures/bd/reuben.p2","order":".000.3434"},"Although Reuben was the firstborn of Jacob and Leah, he lost his birthright because of transgression (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/35.22"},"Gen. 35:22"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/49.3-4"},"49:3–4"],"). The blessing therefore came upon Joseph, the firstborn of Jacob and Rachel (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/5.1-2"},"1 Chr. 5:1–2"],")."]]],"refs":null}
